You are here: Salesforce Help > Docs > Analytics > Learn Your Way Around CRM Analytics for Android

The Home Screen is the first thing you see when you open CRM Analytics on your mobile device. The header has lists of apps, dashboards, lenses, and datasets.

In the header, you can access:
* Lists of your apps, dashboards, lenses, and datasets
* Navigation to change settings, get help, and log out
* Search

Navigation Menu
Open the navigation menu by tapping . You can:
* Change settings
* Send feedback
* Get help
* Log out of your org

At the bottom of the lens screen, you can access the toolbar to explore and filter data.

A Few Simple Gestures
Swipe up: Scroll down lists and dashboard
Swipe down: Scroll up lists and dashboard
Refresh lists when at the top of the list
Swipe left/Right: Flip between screens or asset filters
Scroll: Use one finger to scroll a dashboard; use two fingers to scroll over a scrolling widget
